    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-10-08</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-11-04T19:50:14Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Helping Invigorate and Revive our Economy Act of 2009 or the HIRE America Act - Amends Internal Revenue Code provisions relating to the work opportunity tax credit to: (1) increase the rate of such credit to 50% for members of a targeted group and allow a credit for 30% of wages paid to individuals who are not members of a targeted group; (2) increase the rate of such credit for part-time workers; (3) increase the dollar limitation on the wages eligible for such credit for disabled veterans and summer youth employees; and (4) make such credit permanent. </p> <p>Increases the rate of the tax credit for employer-provided child care. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
